Privacy Policy for WExcel





WExcel (“the App”, “we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our app.


1. Information We Collect

We do not collect, store, or share any personal data from users.

All WhatsApp messages processed by the app remain on your device and are only converted into Excel format at your request.



2. Advertising and Third-Party Services

WExcel uses Google AdMob to display ads. AdMob may collect device identifiers, usage data, and location information for ad targeting in accordance with their own policies.

Please review Google AdMob Privacy Policy
 for details.

In-app purchases are processed by the Google Play Store. We do not have access to your payment or billing information.



3. GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation – EU/EEA Users)

If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have the following rights under GDPR:

The right to access and receive a copy of your personal data.

The right to request correction or deletion of your data.

The right to restrict or object to the processing of your data.

The right to withdraw consent at any time, if applicable.

Since WExcel does not collect personal data, these rights generally do not apply. However, any data processed by third parties (such as Google AdMob) is subject to their privacy practices.



4. CCPA & CPRA (California Residents)

Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA), California residents have the right to:

Know what categories of personal information are collected, used, or disclosed.

Request deletion of personal information.

Opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information.

Not be discriminated against for exercising their privacy rights.

WExcel does not sell personal information. Any data collected through ads (Google AdMob) is handled according to Google’s policies.



5. CalOPPA (California Online Privacy Protection Act)

As required by CalOPPA:

Users can access this Privacy Policy at any time through the app store listing or within the app.

Any future updates to this Privacy Policy will be clearly posted with the new effective date.

We do not collect personally identifiable information directly from users.



6. Children’s Privacy

WExcel is not directed at children under 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

Ads may be personalized depending on Google AdMob settings. Parents may restrict ad personalization via Google account settings.



7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted within the app or on our official listing, and the “Last updated” date will be revised.



8. Contact Us

If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Mohammedalrehaili22@gmail.com
